Yes, you can have individual colors per component. Each lualine component is its own "slot", so each one gets its own `color` setting.

In your current setup, `primary` is a single component that builds the whole string internally, so it only has one color. To get multi-color within the bar, you'd return multiple components instead:

```lua
---@return lualine_component[]
function M.lualine_components()
    local components = {}

    -- component 1: threshold icon
    table.insert(components, {
        function()
            local level, _ = local_share.get_log_threshold()
            return LEVEL_ICONS[level:lower()] or level
        end,
        color = function()
            return { fg = '#FF1493' } -- pink
        end,
        separator = { left = ' ', right = ' ' },
    })

    -- component 2: FIM model
    table.insert(components, {
        function()
            local fim_model = local_share.get_fim_model()
            return fim_model
        end,
        color = function()
            return { fg = '#2EBE10' } -- green
        end,
        separator = { left = ' ', right = ' ' },
    })

    -- add more as needed...

    return components
end
```

Each returned component renders as a separate segment with its own color. You control spacing via `separator`.
